  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Can I make a voice call from my iPad using Jio SIM?",
  "response": "To make a voice call from your iPad using a Jio SIM, you need to consider a few things:\n\n1. **iPad Model**: iPads do not have a built-in cellular radio capable of making traditional voice calls like a smartphone. However, some iPad models do support cellular data through a SIM card.\n\n2. **Jio SIM and Data**: If your iPad is a cellular model, you can insert a Jio SIM to access the internet. Jio offers data plans but does not provide traditional voice call services directly through the SIM on an iPad.\n\n3. **Workarounds**:\n   - **Apps**: You can use internet-based calling apps like WhatsApp, Skype, or JioChat to make voice and video calls over the internet. These apps use VoIP (Voice over Internet Protocol) technology.\n   - **Jio4GVoice App**: Jio offers the Jio4GVoice app, but it is primarily designed for Android devices. There isn't an official version for iPad, but you could try using an Android emulator on your iPad if you're technically inclined (though this is not straightforward or recommended for most users).\n\n4. **Continuity**: If you own an iPhone with the same Apple ID, you can use the Continuity feature to make and receive calls on your iPad. This doesn't use the Jio SIM in the iPad but rather routes calls through your iPhone.\n\nIn summary, you cannot make traditional voice calls directly from an iPad using a Jio SIM. However, you can use internet-based calling apps over the Jio data connection to make voice calls.",
